# Interpreter frame stack-walk scenario.
#
# Activated only when SOS_TEST_INTERPRETER=true (config.TestInterpreter). The test
# launches the InterpreterStackTest debuggee with DOTNET_Interpreter=* so user methods
# are executed by the CoreCLR interpreter. We then verify SOS surfaces the [InterpreterFrame:]
# sentinel that the runtime emits at JIT/interpreter transitions, and that the user frames
# appear under it.
#
# Requires a CoreCLR build with FEATURE_INTERPRETER (Debug/Checked).

CONTINUE

LOADSOS

# Verify the exception itself was correctly captured.
SOSCOMMAND:PrintException
VERIFY:Exception object:\s+<HEXVAL>\s+
VERIFY:Exception type:\s+System\.InvalidOperationException\s+
VERIFY:Message:\s+(<Invalid Object>|Throwing from interpreted frame:.*)\s+
VERIFY:HResult:\s+80131509

# Verify ClrStack walks through the InterpreterFrame sentinel and surfaces the
# interpreted user methods. The [InterpreterFrame: <hex>] line is the runtime's
# JIT<->interpreter transition marker; if interpreter support is missing or the env
# var did not take effect, this VERIFY fails (and the user frames would appear as
# normal JIT frames without the sentinel).
SOSCOMMAND:ClrStack
VERIFY:.*OS Thread Id:\s+0x<HEXVAL>\s+.*
VERIFY:\s+Child\s+SP\s+IP\s+Call Site\s+
VERIFY:\s+<HEXVAL>\s+<HEXVAL>\s+\[InterpreterFrame:\s+<HEXVAL>\].*
VERIFY:\s+<HEXVAL>\s+<HEXVAL>\s+InterpreterUserHelper\.InterpTestMethodThrow.*
VERIFY:\s+<HEXVAL>\s+<HEXVAL>\s+InterpreterUserHelper\.InterpTestMethodRunNested.*
VERIFY:\s+<HEXVAL>\s+<HEXVAL>\s+InterpreterStackTestApp\.Main.*
